"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862107","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-19","<p>NHS Digital publishes information on workforce statistics and the following table shows the full time equivalent (fte) figures for child and adolescent psychiatrists in the last two years.</p><p> </p><p>NHS Hospital and Community Health Services (HCHS): Child and Adolescent Psychiatrists in the North West as at 30 September each specified year and latest month available (fte)</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Child and Adolescent Psychiatrists (fte)</p></td><td><p>September 2015</p></td><td><p>September 2016</p></td><td><p>September 2017</p></td><td><p>November 2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Health Education North West</p></td><td><p>113</p></td><td><p>110</p></td><td><p>118</p></td><td><p>119</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: NHS Digital Monthly HCHS workforce statistics</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","132664","2018-03-19T17:17:52.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862107/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862107/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862107/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-14","Psychiatry: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many NHS child and adolescent psychiatrists have been employed in the North West in the last two years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","132526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862108","Treasury","false","2018-03-19","<p>Since the start of the 2015 Parliament, increases to the personal allowance (up to £11,850 in 2018-19) are expected to cut income tax for 2.8 million individuals in the South West, which includes Gloucestershire and the Parliamentary Constituency of Thornbury and Yate.</p><p> </p><p>These estimates are based on the 2014-15 Survey of Personal Incomes, projected using economic assumptions consistent with the Office for Budget Responsibility’s November 2017 Economic and Fiscal Outlook.</p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury does not publish this information at constituency level or unitary authority level.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","132528 ; 132529","2018-03-19T14:07:28.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862108/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862108/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862108/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-14","Income Tax: Thornbury and Yate","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in the Thornbury and Yate constituency his Department estimates will benefit from the rise in tax free personal allowance during the 2018-2019 financial year.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","132527"
