"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862169","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-21","<p>We are working with the Law Commissions on how best to implement the recommendations of their review of electoral law.</p><p>We have agreed with the Law Commissions and key electoral stakeholders possible means of effecting reform through the drafting of secondary legislation. Work is underway on this by the Law Commissions, who will be supported by Cabinet Office and the Electoral Commission.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-03-21T11:32:36.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862169/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862169/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862169/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-14","Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps his Department is taking to simplify electoral law.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","132588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862170","Department for International Trade","false","2018-03-20","<p>We are working closely with the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy and the UK steel and aluminium industries to assess the potential direct and indirect impacts of these measures.</p><p> </p><p>The President of the United States of America announced there would be a mechanism for U.S. parties to apply for exclusion of specific products based on demand that is unmet by domestic production or on specific national security considerations. Details of this process are yet to be announced.</p><p>We are working closely with UK industry to help support them with this process via their US customers.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","132621","2018-03-20T10:52:46.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862170/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862170/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862170/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-03-14","Iron and Steel: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what estimate his Department has made of the volume of steel that will be re-directed to the UK which would have otherwise gone to the US as a result of the recent announcement on steel tariffs by the US administration.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","132589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862171","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>Local authorities have the power to require schools to allow their premises to be used as polling stations during an election. They must use this power reasonably. Whether or not a school closes or remains open in these circumstances is a decision for the head teacher.</p><p> </p><p>Head teachers’ decisions about closure will depend upon whether arrangements can be made for voting to take place discretely within their school. It may be possible for a school to remain open if pupils and the voting public can be kept apart, with a separate entrance and exit with no compromise to the school's controlled access.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-03-22T16:57:45.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862171/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862171/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862171/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Schools: Polling Stations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps his Department is taking to address concerns over interruption to schooling arising from the use of schools as polling places ahead of the local government elections in May.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","132590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862172","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-19","<p>Pre-existing charges on property have no impact on the SMI loans process. SMI loans will be offered to all eligible claimants regardless of any pre-existing charges on property.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-03-19T12:29:31.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862172/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862172/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862172/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-14","Mortgages: Government Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February 2018 to Question 125704, on Mortgages: Interest Payments, how the application process for the new loan will operate in cases where there is an existing charge on the property.","false","Biography information for Jo Swinson","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","132591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862173","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-22","<p>The Department requested the information from NHS Business Services Authority when Question 128033 was tabled.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-03-22T17:27:15.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862173/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862173/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862173/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-14","Prescription Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 27 February 2018 to Question 128033, on prescription drugs, when his Department first became aware of the NHS Business Services Authority data showing the number of unique patients prescribed (a) benzodiazepines and (b) z drugs.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","132592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862174","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>A public consultation on the criteria for level two childcare qualifications ran from 7 December 2017 to 28 February 2018. The consultation document can be found at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://consult.education.gov.uk/childcare-providers-and-regulation/improving-level-2-qualifications-for-the-early-edu/supporting_documents/Level%202%20Qualification%20Criteria%20Consultation%20Document%2006%2011%202017%20Accessible%20FINAL.pdf" target="_blank">https://consult.education.gov.uk/childcare-providers-and-regulation/improving-level-2-qualifications-for-the-early-edu/supporting_documents/Level%202%20Qualification%20Criteria%20Consultation%20Document%2006%2011%202017%20Accessible%20FINAL.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The government’s response to the public consultation will be published in due course.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T16:58:41.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862174/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862174/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862174/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what progress has been made on the commitment in the Early Years Workforce Strategy 2017 to develop criteria for the content of level two childcare qualifications; how many meetings have taken place with the childcare sector and awarding organisations; and who attended such meetings.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862175","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The following changes to our early years data collections have been implemented.</p><p> </p><p>In the 2018 Survey of Childcare and Early Years Providers we have:</p><ul><li>Added a question about gender of the paid workforce, which was not asked in 2016.</li><li>Improved the questions on ethnicity, by introducing more granular categories for responses and we are asking about the ethnicity of apprentices for the first time.</li><li>Improved the wording around staff qualifications in the survey to also include relevant teaching qualifications.</li></ul><p> </p><p>The 2018 Early Years Census asks for a wider range of information on staff qualifications than in previous years, specifically level 2 and 3 staff and those with graduate qualifications (early years professional status, early years teacher status and qualified teacher status).</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T17:08:14.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862175/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862175/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862175/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what changes have been made to his Department's existing data collection as a result of the commitment to review workforce data in the Early years Workforce Strategy 2017.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862176","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The Initial Teacher Training (ITT) Census publishes experimental statistics on the number of new entrants to Early Years ITT, including a breakdown by route. Data going back to academic year 2016/17 are available in the latest ITT Census publication, available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2017-to-2018</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The department is unable to provide any data collected prior to the experimental statistics released with the ITT Census on 24 November 2016.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","132596 ; 132601","2018-03-22T17:32:59.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862176/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862176/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862176/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many people have been awarded early years teacher status in each year since 2013.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862177","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The Initial Teacher Training (ITT) Census publishes experimental statistics on the number of new entrants to Early Years ITT, including a breakdown by route. Data going back to academic year 2016/17 are available in the latest ITT Census publication, available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2017-to-2018</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The department is unable to provide any data collected prior to the experimental statistics released with the ITT Census on 24 November 2016.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","132595 ; 132601","2018-03-22T17:32:59.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862177/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862177/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862177/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many people have taken part in early years initial teacher training in each year since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862178","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p><p>The number of new entrants to initial teacher training ITT is published in the annual ITT Census, which since 2016/17, has included experimental statistics on the number of trainees starting Early Years ITT programmes. The census is available to view here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-teacher-training" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-teacher-training</a>.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T17:28:15.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862178/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862178/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862178/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many early years teacher trainees who have started an early years teacher qualification have switched to initial teacher training to become a qualified teacher in each year since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862179","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The following table provides the average salaries of full and part-time teachers in service in state funded nursery and primary schools, state funded secondary schools and state funded special schools in England in November 2013 to 2016.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>State Funded Nursery and Primary</strong></p></td><td><p>£36,200</p></td><td><p>£36,300</p></td><td><p>£36,600</p></td><td><p>£37,200</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>State Funded Secondary</strong></p></td><td><p>£38,000</p></td><td><p>£38,300</p></td><td><p>£38,700</p></td><td><p>£39,500</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>State Funded Special</strong></p></td><td><p>£39,800</p></td><td><p>£39,900</p></td><td><p>£39,900</p></td><td><p>£40,300</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Source: School Workforce Census</em></p><p>Figures are rounded to the nearest £100.</p><p> </p><p>The information for November 2015 and 2016 is publicly available in Table 9a in each annual statistical first release ‘School Workforce in England’ available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-school-workforce" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-school-workforce</a>.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-03-22T16:12:36.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862179/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862179/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862179/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Teachers: Average Earnings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average salary of an (a) early years, (b) primary school, (3) secondary school and (d) special school teacher was in each year since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132598"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862180","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The information requested is not held centrally for teachers going through Initial Teacher Training (ITT).</p><p> </p><p>Statutory guidance for accredited ITT providers, including for employment-based ITT routes where trainee teachers earn a salary whilst they train: “For the period of training all applicants must be employed as unqualified teachers at a school, and (except applicants employed in academies or independent schools) must be paid in accordance with at least point one on the unqualified teachers’ pay scale for the period of their training”.</p><p> </p><p>The minimum of the unqualified teachers’ pay range is specified in the school teachers’ pay and conditions document. The below table shows this for each year from 2013 to 2017. Employment-based trainees who are employed in maintained schools must be paid at least the minimum of this range. Academies or independent schools are not required to follow this range, although they may choose to do so.</p><p> </p><p>Minimum of unqualified teacher pay range – 2013 to 2017</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>England and Wales <br>(excluding the <br>London Area) £</p></td><td><p>Inner<br>London<br>Area £</p></td><td><p>Outer <br>London<br> Area £</p></td><td><p>Fringe<br> Area £</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Minimum from 1 September 2013</p></td><td><p>15,976</p></td><td><p>20,092</p></td><td><p>18,977</p></td><td><p>17,025</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Minimum from 1 September 2014</p></td><td><p>16,136</p></td><td><p>20,293</p></td><td><p>19,167</p></td><td><p>17,196</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Minimum from 1 September 2015</p></td><td><p>16,298</p></td><td><p>20,496</p></td><td><p>19,359</p></td><td><p>17,368</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Minimum from 1 September 2016</p></td><td><p>16,461</p></td><td><p>20,701</p></td><td><p>19,553</p></td><td><p>17,542</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Minimum from 1 September 2017</p></td><td><p>16,626</p></td><td><p>20,909</p></td><td><p>19,749</p></td><td><p>17,718</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Source: </em><em>School teachers' pay and conditions documents</em></p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-03-22T15:31:49.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862180/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862180/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862180/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Teachers: Average Earnings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average salary of a trainee (a) early years, (b) primary school, (c) secondary school and (d) special school teacher was in each year since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862181","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Whilst the average salary in not available, general information on salaries of full and part-time teachers in service in state funded nursery and primary schools, state funded secondary schools and state funded special schools are publicly available in Table 9a within the statistical first release ‘School Workforce in England, November 2016’, available at the following web link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/school-workforce-in-england-november-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/school-workforce-in-england-november-2016</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-03-22T16:21:20.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862181/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862181/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862181/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Teachers: Average Earnings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average salary of an (a) early years, (b) primary school, (c) secondary school and (d) special school teacher was five years after they started teaching.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862182","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The Initial Teacher Training (ITT) Census publishes experimental statistics on the number of new entrants to Early Years ITT, including a breakdown by route. Data going back to academic year 2016/17 are available in the latest ITT Census publication, available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2017-to-2018</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The department is unable to provide any data collected prior to the experimental statistics released with the ITT Census on 24 November 2016.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","132595 ; 132596","2018-03-22T17:32:59.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862182/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862182/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862182/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many early years teachers have trained through each of the four teacher training routes referred to in paragraph 24 of the Early Years Workforce Strategy 2017 since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862183","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T16:22:28.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862183/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862183/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862183/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many and what proportion of graduates who were already employed in an early years setting have undertaken early years initial teacher training in each year since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132602"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862184","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>In academic year 2016/17, there were 110 trainees undertaking either the Graduate Entry or School Direct postgraduate route to Early Years Initial Teacher Training (ITT). Bursaries are payable subject to eligibility criteria; the bursary amount paid to providers in 2016/17 was £394,600.</p><p> </p><p>Information from periods prior to 2016/17 is not held centrally.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T17:21:55.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862184/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862184/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862184/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many bursaries have been provided to trainee early years teachers in each year since September 2013; and what the average amount was of those bursaries.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862185","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-19","<p>This Government is committed to making giving as easy and compelling as possible.</p><p> </p><p>In 2017 we launched the Small Charities Fundraising Training Programme, delivered by a partnership led by the Foundation for Social Improvement. This will provide over 5,000 subsidised fundraising training opportunities for small charities. As part of this offer over 600 opportunities have been made available for charities to develop their digital skills and online presence, with a further 1,000 opportunities to be made available next year.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-03-19T15:02:31.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862185/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862185/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862185/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-14","Charities: Fund Raising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what support his Department is providing to charities to improve their digital fundraising infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","132604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862186","Home Office","false","2018-03-19","<p>I announced the police funding settlement for 2018-19 which will see an additional £450m invested in the policing system, around £270m direct to PCCs. This strong and comprehensive settlement combined with the current levels of reserves will enable the vast majority of PCCs to protect or improve frontline policing.</p><p>As at March 2017, PCCs held over £1.6bn of public money in usable resource reserves, significantly more than in 2010-11. Reserves are an important tool for police leaders, but this is taxpayers’ money and we need real transparency about how it is being used. That is why in January the Government published information on police reserves and provided guidance to PCCs making clear that they must be more open with taxpayers about their plans to use them.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-03-19T13:13:05.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862186/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862186/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862186/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-14","Police: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effect of changes in the level of police funding on the ability of police forces to maintain financial reserves.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","132605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862187","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T16:18:08.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862187/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862187/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862187/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many early years teachers who have previously received an early years bursary remain an early years teacher working in a maintained setting.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862188","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The early years initial teacher training (EYITT) routes are demand-led and we have always met the needs of EYITT providers in terms of numbers of places they have requested. EYITT providers have confirmed the allocation of places they would like to request for the academic year 2018/19.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T17:00:05.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862188/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862188/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862188/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much funding has been made available for early years teacher training courses in each year since September 2013; and how much funding will be made available in the next three years.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862189","Department for Education","false","2018-03-20","<p>Poor body image is a factor in eating disorders and other mental health problems. The additional £1.4 billion the Government is making available for children and young people’s mental health services up to 2020, includes £150 million specifically targeted at improving support for young people with eating disorders. The green paper ‘Transforming children and young people’s mental health provision’ set out proposals for new mental health support teams to provide further trained and clinically-supervised support to young people in school.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has also funded the provision of information and advice to schools. MindEd (<a href="https://www.minded.org.uk/" target="_blank">https://www.minded.org.uk/</a>) is a free online portal that provides training for all adults working with children and young people about mental health problems. It includes specific information on eating disorders. The Personal, Social, Health and Economic (PSHE) Association has also produced advice on how to teach pupils in all four Key Stages about mental health. This includes specific advice on age-appropriate teaching about body image and eating disorders in secondary school.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has sought views, via a thorough engagement process, on the content of Relationships Education and Relationships and Sex Education, and on the status of PSHE – including on issues such as body image and eating disorders. The findings will inform draft regulations and guidance for schools, which will be subject to further consultation.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-03-20T17:52:50.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862189/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862189/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862189/answer","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862189/answer/previousversion/48388","Biography information for Nick Gibb","60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pupils: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps his Department is taking to tackle (a) eating disorders and (b) body image issues among young people in schools.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","132608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862190","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>For the academic year 2017/18, £3,017,000 has been allocated to nursery employers to help support trainees on the Graduate Employment Based route for Early Years ITT.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T14:10:57.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862190/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862190/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862190/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much funding has been allocated to nursery employers to help those employers support graduates in their settings to become early years teachers.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132609"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862191","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The current list of accredited providers of early years initial teacher training (EYITT) in England is published here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/early-years-initial-teacher-training-itt-providers-and-school-direct-early-years-lead-organisations/early-years-initial-teacher-training-itt-providers-and-school-direct-lead-organisations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/early-years-initial-teacher-training-itt-providers-and-school-direct-early-years-lead-organisations/early-years-initial-teacher-training-itt-providers-and-school-direct-lead-organisations</a>.</p><p>EYITT providers are listed by region and information is given on which of the training routes they offer; all of which lead to early year’s teacher status (EYTS) upon successful completion. The four routes to EYTS are graduate entry, graduate employment-based, undergraduate, and assessment only.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally there are courses provided at levels 2 and 3 in early years education and care. In the year 2016/17, 186 providers delivered level 2 and 952 providers delivered level 3.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T17:01:23.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862191/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862191/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862191/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many training providers there are for (a) level two, (b) level three and (c) graduate early years teacher training routes.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132610"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862192","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>Visits to the landing pages for early years, primary, and secondary on the Get Into Teaching website since its relaunch by financial year are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Financial year 2015-16 (from 20 Apr 2015)</p></td><td><p>Financial year 2016-17</p></td><td><p>Financial year 2017-18 (to 14 Mar 2018)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total page views Early years landing page</p></td><td><p>253,485</p></td><td><p>264,673</p></td><td><p>163,151</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total page views Primary landing page</p></td><td><p>94,227</p></td><td><p>90,284</p></td><td><p>91,806</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total page views Secondary landing page</p></td><td><p>73,046</p></td><td><p>94,194</p></td><td><p>92,242</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total page views Website ALL</p></td><td><p>11,468,147</p></td><td><p>14,415,489</p></td><td><p>12,940,487</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total web visits (sessions)</p></td><td><p>3,744,756</p></td><td><p>5,055,511</p></td><td><p>4,691,802</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Source: Google Analytics, 14 March 2018.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T14:33:32.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862192/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862192/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862192/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Department for Education: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many visits the landing page for the specific early years area on the Get into teaching website had in each year since that website was launched compared with the equivalent landing page for (a) primary teaching and (b) secondary teaching.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862193","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>The marketing budget for recruitment to post-graduate initial teacher training for the financial year 2017-18 is £15.2 million. There is no budget breakdown between primary and secondary recruitment.</p><p> </p><p>The marketing budget for recruitment to the separate early years teaching entry route for the financial year 2017-18 is £100,000.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-03-22T17:05:05.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862193/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862193/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862193/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Teachers: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the annual marketing budget is for recruiting (a) early years, (b) primary and (c) secondary school teachers.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862194","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>Last year the department conducted an internal policy review of the early years initial teacher training (EYITT) routes. Following the policy review we made the decision to close the School Direct EYITT route. This particular route was delivered as a pilot but did not attract sufficient interest from potential applicants to be viable in the long term. However, we continue to provide alternative EYITT routes for graduates and undergraduates.</p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T17:26:07.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862194/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862194/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862194/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when his Department plans to publish the results of the review into early years initial teacher training announced in the Early Years Workforce Strategy 2017.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862195","Department for Education","false","2018-03-22","<p>We are considering a range of approaches to supporting graduates in the early years workforce – including in disadvantaged areas. This work is still underway and further information will be made available in due course.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-22T16:54:15.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862195/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862195/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862195/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-14","Pre-school Education: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Early Years Workforce Strategy 2017, what progress has been made on the feasibility study due to report in March 2018 into developing a programme that specifically seeks to grow the graduate workforce in disadvantaged areas.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","132614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862196","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-19","<p>​Officials from the Foreign and Commonwealth Office, the Department for International Development and our Embassy in Washington attended this meeting. The UK remains gravely concerned about the humanitarian situation in Gaza. We welcome all practical steps to improve conditions as a matter of urgency.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-19T15:36:05.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862196/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862196/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862196/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-14","Gaza: International Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government was represented at the US-led meeting at the White House on 13 March 2018 on the humanitarian crisis in Gaza; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","132615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862197","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-19","<p>No funding has yet been awarded via the Cultural Development Fund. We will announce further details in due course.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis","132617","2018-03-19T16:45:49.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862197/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862197/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/862197/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-14","Cultural Heritage: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, which projects have (a) been funded by and (b) had funding approved from the Cultural Development Fund; and what the overall value is of that funding for those projects.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","132616"
